@node "Info_and_System_Requirements" "Info and System Requirements"

 EasyReqPatch is a small commodity which makes system requesters pointer relative. Or
better, the button strip of the requester is centered under the mouse pointer.
 I have used this solution because the pointer doesn't cover any part of the text and
the buttons are nearer to the pointer itself (and if the requester contains only one
gadget, you need only to click the mouse button).

 It works only under AmigaOS 3.x and requires a 68020 or better processor.
@endnode

@node "How_to_use" "How to use"

 You can start EasyReqPatch either from cli or workbench. Currently there are no
parameters or tooltypes (except DONOTWAIT if you put the program in the WBStartup
drawer).

 You can simply launch EasyReqPatch again to remove it.

 Moreover it is a commodity, so you can control it even with the Commodity Exchange
program. Use the 'remove' button to quit it or the 'inactive' button to disable it
temporarily (then use 'active' to reactivate it). It's very easy.

 Note: EasyReqPatch patches two AmigaOS functions to work (EasyRequestArgs and
OpenWindowTagList), if any other program patches these two functions after
EasyReqPatch, you can't quit until you remove the other programs.
 If you run programs like SetMan or PatchControl (this one is included in the MCP
package) you can remove EasyReqPatch at any time.
@endnode

@node "History" "History"

 @{b}Version 1.0@{ub}

    NOTE       First release


 @{b}Version 1.01@{ub}

    CHANGED    Compiled with SAS/C 6.55
    CHANGED    Small optimizations, now the program is a bit smaller


 @{b}Version 1.02@{ub}

    CHANGED    Now works with any processor.
    FIXED      The commodity title contained too many brackets.
    ADDED      Added italian documentation.
    CHANGED    New history format.

 @{b}Version 1.3@{ub}

    CHANGED    Reduced code size.
    CHANGED    Reduced stack size.
    CHANGED    Compiled with SAS/C 6.57.
    CHANGED    Now uses the standard AmigaOS version format.
    CHANGED    Requires a 68020.
@endnode

